ecting the derivation of the appellation thus applied are also mentioned by various authors.] ―         -b5-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "masiyHN", "text_ar": "مَسِيحٌ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Sweat:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, S, K:) so called because it is wiped off ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yumosaHu", "text_ar": "يُمْسَحُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ") when it pours forth. (T.) ―         -b6-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "masiyHN", "text_ar": "مَسِيحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  A dirhem [or silver coin]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of which the impression is obliterated;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aTolasu", "text_ar": "اَطْلَسُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, Msb, K;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "having no impression."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb.) ―         -b7-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "masiyHN", "text_ar": "مَسِيحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "masiyHapN", "text_ar": "مَسِيحَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A piece of silver."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As, S, K.) ―         -b8-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "masiyHN", "text_ar": "مَسِيحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mamosuwHu Alwajohi", "text_ar": "مَمْسُوحُ الوَجْهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) i.e., A man"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "having one side of his face plain, without eye"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "eyebrow:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "said to apply in this sense to EdDejjál, among others. (IF, L.) ―         -b9-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "One-eyed."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Az.) [See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^amosaHu", "text_ar": "اَمْسَحُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] ―         -b10-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "tex